cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically image denoising and segmentation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks and loss functions, which are common topics in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper proposes an unsupervised approach, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of image sets and experiments also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
